- 'single-family homes built in the new millennium' refers to properties built after the year 2000;
- 'blossomed' refers to the successful sale of properties;
- 'within a month' means the sale duration is 30 days or less;
- 'average yield' refers to the average sale price of the properties.

- "tended to more than five unique plots of land" refers to selling more than 5 unique properties;
- "total area they have cultivated" refers to the sum of the lot sizes of the sold properties;
- "average size of their plots" refers to the average square footage of the sold properties;
- "gardeners (agents)" refers to the unique real estate agents involved in the sales;
- "total value of their harvest (sales)" refers to the total sales amount of the properties.

- "top 5 stars" refers to the top 5 real estate agents based on their total sales amount;
- "real estate galaxy" refers to the real estate market or industry;
- "shone brighter than the $1,000,000 mark" means the team's total sales amount exceeds $1,000,000.

- "reigns supreme in sales" refers to the team with the highest total sales amount;
- "like a king on a throne" is a metaphor for the top-ranked team;
- "average price per square foot" is a measure of the typical cost of properties sold by the team.

- "Titans of the market" refers to teams with total sales exceeding $5,000,000;
- "Raking in" is a metaphorical expression meaning to earn or accumulate a significant amount of money;
- "Average sale price" is the mean price of all properties sold by the team.

- 'Blossomed into seasoned professionals' refers to agents who have completed more than 10 sales;
- 'Achieved mastery' refers to brokers who have completed more than 50 sales;
- 'Priced at a premium' refers to properties with a sale price greater than $500,000;
- 'Offer exceptional value' refers to properties with a price per square foot greater than $200.

- 'top agents' refers to those with the highest total sales amount;
- 'more than average sales' means their total sales are greater than the average total sales of all agents;
- 'earned' refers to the total sales amount.

- "blossomed with more than one flower" refers to neighborhoods with more than one sale;
- "average prices" refers to the average sale price;
- "number of blossoms" refers to the number of sales;
- "average time it takes for a flower to bloom" refers to the average sale duration.

- "Top 5 agents" refers to the agents with the highest total sales amounts;
- "Most recent sale before the start of 2023" means the latest sale date before January 1, 2023;
- "Outperform the average sales amount" means the total sales amount is greater than the average total sales amount across all sales.
